      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/4/25/25",
      "text": [
        " بَعْضُ أَصْحَابِ اَلنَّبِيِّ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ يَا رَسُولَ اَللَّهِ مَا بَالُنَا نَجِدُ بِأَوْلاَدِنَا مَا لاَ يَجِدُونَ بِنَا فَقَالَ \"لِأَنَّهُمْ مِنْكُمْ وَ لَسْتُمْ مِنْهُمْ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4923 - Some of the companions of the Prophet (peace be upon him and his family) asked: \"O Messenger of Allah (swt), why do we feel a stronger affection for our children than they feel for us?\"\nHe (sw) replied: \"Because they are from you, but you are not from them.\""
        ]
      }
    },
